In all of your replies/posts on supporting ES6 you've only really mentioned a few features of ES6 (e.g. generics and modules). Will there be a point in the future where we will be able to compile to ES6 and use things like generators?<br />
<br />
I.e. I'm talking about being able to write:<br />
<div style="color:Black;background-color:White;"><pre>
<span style="color:Blue;">function</span> * mygenerator() {
    <span style="color:Blue;">var</span> x = 1;
    <span style="color:Blue;">while</span> (<span style="color:Blue;">true</span>) {
        yield x;
        x += x;
    }
}
</pre></div>Without typescript errors.<br />
<br />
I don't expect TypeScript to try and fancily compile the generator function so that it works with older versions of JavaScript, I just want typing support for my ES6 projects.<br />
